cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of predicting website safety ratings using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these fields are closely related to the topic of web reputation systems and machine learning. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel ensemble classification technique, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of structural and content-based properties of websites, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
